{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/anguttara-nikaya/AN3/155-pubbanhasutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>“Mendicants, those sentient beings who do good things in the morning by way of body, speech, and mind have a good morning. </p>\n<p>Those sentient beings who do good things at midday by way of body, speech, and mind have a good midday. </p>\n<p>Those sentient beings who do good things in the evening by way of body, speech, and mind have a good evening. </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A good star, a good fortune, <br>\na good dawn, a good rising, <br>\na good moment, a good hour: <br>\nthese come with good gifts to spiritual practitioners. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Worthy deeds of body, <br>\nverbal worthy deeds, <br>\nworthy deeds of mind, <br>\nworthy resolutions: <br>\nwhen your deeds have been worthy, <br>\nyou get worthy benefits. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Those happy with these benefits <br>\nflourish in the Buddha’s teaching. <br>\nMay you and all your relatives <br>\nbe healthy and happy!” </p>\n</blockquote>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/anguttara-nikaya/AN3/156-162/\">AN.3.156–162 </a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“Mendicants, those sentient beings who do good things in the morning by way of body, speech, and mind have a good morning. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Those sentient beings who do good things at midday by way of body, speech, and mind have a good midday. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Those sentient beings who do good things in the evening by way of body, speech, and mind have a good evening. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"